# Model routing

Match delegation to task type. Do not use `generalPurpose` for simple search or shell work.

## Built-in subagents (prefer these)

| Task | Use | Why |
|------|-----|-----|
| File search, codebase map, keyword lookup | `explore` | Product-optimized fast exploration |
| Terminal, git, npm, CI, scripts | `shell` | Isolated command execution |
| Bug-focused review (user asks) | `bugbot` | Specialized review |
| Security review (user asks) | `security-review` | Specialized review |
| Multi-step implementation needing varied tools | `generalPurpose` | Only when no narrower agent fits |

## Custom project agents (`.cursor/agents/`)

| Task | Agent | Model tier |
|------|-------|------------|
| Team exploration rules | `explorer` | fast |
| Code review before PR / after edits | `reviewer` | balanced-thinking |
| Write or fix tests | `tester` | balanced |
| Security audit (if installed) | `security-auditor` | high-thinking |
| Architecture / migration (if installed) | `architect` | high-thinking |
| Docs (if installed) | `docs-writer` | fast |

When launching custom agents via Task, pass the `model` from the agent frontmatter.

## Rules

1. Search → `explore` or `explorer`, not `generalPurpose`
2. Commands → `shell`, not main session
3. Review → `reviewer` or `bugbot`, not full parent model by default
4. Reserve premium models for security and architecture work
